description:
The Center for the Integration & Advancement of New Americans (CIANA) is a social services organization located in NYC in Astoria, Queens. We work to integrate new immigrants from the Middle East/North Africa, South Asia, Latin America, and West Africa, into the socio-economic and civic life of American society while maintaining pride in their cultural heritage.

We are seeking a well-organized, gregarious, and detail-oriented self-starter to join our case management team to provide services to our newly arrived immigrant and refugee families with job/housing assistance, public benefits, education support, healthcare enrollment, information and referrals, and general case management services.

* At least one year of completed college education;
* Fluency in Arabic and French (speaking, reading, writing), other languages a plus;
* Strong organizational skills;
* Excellent verbal/written English communication skills;
* Experience in case management;
* Ability to work independently and as part of a team;
* Understanding of immigration issues and ability to work with diverse populations;
* Experience with Microsoft Office and Google Suite.
* Conduct client intakes and psychosocial assessments;
* Monitor client progress, provide case management, casework counseling, and follow-up services;
* Provide translation/interpretation and case conferencing;
* Make referrals to service providers including healthcare, ESL classes, childcare, afterschool programs, immigration legal services, public benefits;
* Prepare, maintain, and update client case records in data management system;
* Attend trainings, meetings, and represent clients at meetings/appointments;
* Advocate and coordinate with service providers, city agencies, and schools on behalf of client families;
* Assist with educational workshops and other tasks as necessary to facilitate delivery of services to clients.

Job Types: Full-time, Temporary

Pay: $18.00 - $20.00 per hour

Expected hours: 35 per week

Schedule:

* Day shift

Ability to Relocate:

* Astoria, NY 11106: Relocate before starting work (Required)

Work Location: In person

Financial Analyst  


We are seeking a motivated **Financial Analyst** to join our team. This is a great opportunity for someone looking to advance their career in Finance. You must be a self-starter with advanced Excel, strong analytical abilities, excellent customer service skills, and attention to detail. Prior experience working in an accounting or finance capacity is a must.  

**Responsibilities include:*** Strategic Profit & Loss Management: Lead in-depth Profit & Loss analysis for existing accounts across multiple companies, identifying trends and providing actionable insights to senior leadership; across 6 companies;
* Reviewing Requests for Proposals and preparing bid submissions; ensuring alignment with organizational goals and maximizing win rates.
* Preparing annual budgets and forecasts; incorporating strategic financial planning and long-term business objectives
* Performing analysis of prospective business; Conduct comprehensive analysis of potential business opportunities, evaluating financial viability and strategic fit for expansion.
* Advanced Financial Reporting: Develop and oversee budget-to-actual reports, offering high-level analysis and recommendations for financial performance improvements and communicating financial details to the management team;
* Management Reporting: Issue high-impact management reports and analyses, highlighting key financial metrics and trends that influence organizational strategy.
* Monthly processing of labor billing; ensuring accuracy and efficiency in financial operations.
* Communicate directly with clients and attend off-site meetings as required, representing the company and fostering strong client relationships.

**Minimum Requirements:*** Bachelor’s degree in accounting, Finance, Business, or a related field;
* Expert-level proficiency in Microsoft Excel, with demonstrated experience in financial modeling and complex data analysis;
* Minimum 3-5 years of experience in similar role;
* Strong analytical skills with a demonstrated ability to synthesize complex financial data and provide strategic recommendations;
* Prior Customer Service Experience a plus;
* Superior professional written and verbal communication skills, with experience presenting financial information to senior executives.

